Few travels are life altering - this one sure was. Sharing a very personal experience in Norway that brought into sharp focus of what value for live really means and why we as Indias need to do better to value and respect life - why we need to extend help to those in need of it. Here's wishing that this month end message makes some sense and a dent in the universe.

comments.text:
🟦 Congress (Before 2014) vs 🟧 BJP (2014–2024)
1. Infrastructure

🟦 Congress:

Highway growth was ~3–4 km/day.

Very few airports added, metros stuck in files.

Power shortage + coal scams.

🟧 BJP:

Highways built ~35 km/day (10x faster).

75+ airports added in 9 years.

Metro in 20+ cities, bullet train project started.

World’s largest solar parks—India 4th in renewables.

2. Laws & Governance

🟦 Congress:

Still using British-era IPC & CrPC (1860s) and Evidence Act.

600+ scattered, outdated labour laws confusing businesses.

Corruption scandals: 2G, CWG, Coal—lakhs of crores lost.

🟧 BJP:

Replaced colonial codes with 3 new criminal codes (2023).

44 labour laws merged into 4 labour codes for workers + industries.

Direct Benefit Transfers (DBT): ₹3 lakh crore saved from leakages.

3. Economy

🟦 Congress:

India was 10th largest economy in 2014 (~$1.9 trillion).

High inflation (10%+) hurting middle class.

Foreign investors hesitant.

🟧 BJP:

India is now 5th largest economy (~$4 trillion).

Inflation kept ~5% average despite global crises.

Record FDI inflows, digital payments revolution (UPI).

4. Labour, Jobs & Welfare

🟦 Congress:

MNREGA (wage scheme) was main flagship.

Middlemen, fake ration cards, ghost beneficiaries.

Health schemes weak, very limited coverage.

🟧 BJP:

Ayushman Bharat: 50 crore people with free health insurance.

PM Awas Yojana: 4 crore houses built for poor.

UPI/Digital India → 400 crore+ daily transactions.

Leakages plugged, poor actually get the benefit.

5. National Security & Global Standing

🟦 Congress:

“Soft” response to terror (26/11, Parliament attack).

Defence imports high, indigenous production low.

Weak presence in global forums.

🟧 BJP:

Surgical & Balakot strikes showed decisive action.

Defence exports jumped 10x (₹21,000 crore in 2023).

G20 presidency, QUAD, BRICS expansion—India seen as global leader.

🔑 Essence

Congress: “Slow growth, colonial laws, corruption, weak image.”

BJP: “Modern infra, strong governance, fastest economy, decisive leadership.”
